::: {#d5f990aa .cell execution_count=28}
``` {.python .cell-code}
def one_update(X):
    for i, x in enumerate(X):
        dist = torch.sqrt(((x-X)**2).sum(1))
#         weight = gaussian(dist, 2.5)
        weight = tri(dist, 8)
        X[i] = (weight[:,None]*X).sum(0)/weight.sum()
```
:::


::: {#c0cabccb .cell execution_count=29}
``` {.python .cell-code}
def meanshift(data):
    X = data.clone()
    for it in range(5): one_update(X)
    return X
```
:::


